title: Stormwater - Flood Control Facilities
description:
A flood control facility refers to any method used to prevent or reduce the 
detrimental effects of flood waters.  This may include, but not limited 
to; planting vegetation, construction of flood ways, levees, lakes, dams, 
reservoirs or retention/detention ponds.

title: ODOT Cities
description:
The city polygon
file illustrates the boundaries of municipal jurisdictions within Ohio.? This file is maintained as a process related
to the updating of the Road Inventory for the distribution of gas tax monies.
This dataset is currently published on an annual basis.

title: Allen Addresses LBRS
description: The State of Ohio Location Based Response System address points depict the access points to addressable structures along public and private roads within participating Ohio Counties. Address point data was developed from data collected by field observation of existing address locations at the time of collection.?View Full Metadata

title: Allen Centerlines LBRS
description: The State of Ohio Location Based Response System road centerlines depict center of pavement of public and private roads within participating Ohio Counties. Address Range data was developed from data collected by field observation of existing address locations at the time of collection.?View Full Metadata
